England started their qualifying campaign for the 2016 European Championships in the perfect manner with a 2-0 victory over Switzerland at St Jakob-Park.

Danny Welbeck netted a brace to see Roy Hodgson's men claim victory in what could prove to be the toughest hurdle on the road to France 2016.

Here, Sportsmail's Neil Ashton and Charles Sale give their verdict on how Hodgson's men performed, with particular praise for Danny Welbeck, Raheem Sterling and Wayne Rooney.

